@yegor256 The password is fine. Even changing google account access for less secure apps didn't make the difference. Now, I tried with Apache Commons Email (v.1.4)

```
        final SimpleEmail email = new SimpleEmail();
        email.setHostName("smtp.gmail.com");
        email.setSmtpPort(465);
        email.setAuthenticator(new DefaultAuthenticator("me@gmail.com", "pass"));
        email.setSSLOnConnect(true);
        email.setFrom("me@gmail.com");
        email.setSubject("TestMail");
        email.setMsg("This is a test mail");
        email.addTo("me@gmail.com");
        email.send();
```

and it works with Apache. So there must be something missing with jcabi-email. (Yes, `me@gmail.com` and `pass` are the same for both email clients).
But as you have no idea what is wrong means it is working for you, isn't it?

Just for the records, this is the jcabi code:

```
final Postman postman = new Postman.Default(
            new SMTP("smtp.gmail.com", 465, "me@gmail.com", "pass")
        );
        postman.send(
            new Envelope.MIME(
                new Array<Stamp>(
                    new StSender("me@gmail.com"),
                    new StRecipient("me@gmail.com"),
                    new StSubject("test from jcabi")
                ),
                new Array<Enclosure>(
                    new EnHTML(
                        "Hello"
                    )
                )
            )
        );
```
